                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='8'>INSIGHTS</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='8'>• Mumbai Indians have won the highest number of IPL matches (144), making them the most successful team in the dataset.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='8'>• Match frequency peaked in 2013 (76 matches) and remained consistently high from 2022–2024.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='8'>• Winning the toss provides only a slight advantage, with both outcomes occurring almost equally.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='8'>• Eden Gardens has hosted the highest number of IPL matches, followed by Wankhede Stadium.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff' fontsize='8'>• AB de Villiers has won the most Player of the Match awards (25), highlighting his consistent match-winning performances.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#f1ce63' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='1' />
